body: "# Semgrep finding import\n\nSemgrep finding id: 874840451\nRule: package_managers.dependabot.dependabot-missing-cooldown.dependabot-missing-cooldown\nProduct: Code\nSeverity: Medium\nStatus: Open\nConfidence: High\nCategory: security\nIs Pro Rule: False\nSemgrep autotriage result: True positive\nSemgrep file risk tag: Build Process\nRepository: unbraind/pm-cli\nBranch: refs/heads/main\nCreated at: 2026-07-03 12:04:25.346159\nLast opened at: 2026-07-03 12:04:25.327857\n\nLinks:\n- Code: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/blob/6f511706628f18743a00a1cfe851e8d1f492684e/.github/dependabot.yml#L23\n- Semgrep: https://semgrep.dev/orgs/unbrained/findings/874840451\n- Repository: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli\n\nRule description:\nThis Dependabot configuration does not set a cooldown period. Newly published packages can be malicious or unstable. Add a `cooldown` block with `default-days: 7` to each `package-ecosystem` entry under `updates` to wait 7 days before proposing updates to newly published package versions. Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/code-security/dependabot/dependabot-version-updates/configuration-options-for-the-dependabot.yml-file#cooldown\n\nImported from downloaded CSV:\n/home/steve/Downloads/Semgrep_Code_Combined_Findings_2026_07_06.csv"
